ENTRY       EC 1.2.1.83                 Enzyme
NAME        3-succinoylsemialdehyde-pyridine dehydrogenase
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the aldehyde or oxo group of donors;
            With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
SYSNAME     4-oxo-4-(pyridin-3-yl)butanal:NADP+ oxidoreductase
REACTION    4-oxo-4-(pyridin-3-yl)butanal + NADP+ + H2O = 4-oxo-4-(pyridin-3-yl)butanoate + NADPH + H+ [RN:R10105]
ALL_REAC    R10105
SUBSTRATE   4-oxo-4-(pyridin-3-yl)butanal [CPD:C19567];
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     4-oxo-4-(pyridin-3-yl)butanoate [CPD:C19569];
            NADPH [CPD:C00005];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     The enzyme has been characterized from the soil bacterium Pseudomonas sp. HZN6. It participates in the nicotine degradation pathway.
